snippet.textDisplay:
If all people would free the animals instead of killing them, if the entire world would practice vegetarianism, then all the world's disasters would disappear, the crisis would be averted.

There isn't any other way to avert a crisis. And this is why... Everything depends on the Mind. If people have wholesome minds, the world will be wholesome. If people have corrupt minds, the world will be corrupt and doomsday will arrive.

Take a look around, and you'll see natural and man-made calamities... floods, hurricanes, fires, and wars... occurring everywhere. Even if we don't count the casualties from the major natural disasters, but only consider the smaller tragedies such as plane crashes, train derailments, and car collisions, the number of fatalities is still staggering.

And now we have this Coronavirus pandemic!

Well, these various catastrophes result from violent tempers and lack of virtue. Yet no one has awakened to this fact. Instead, each blames the other and refuses to take responsibility.

I bet there is not even one single person on earth that has reflected upon himself and thought, "The world is not in good shape because I haven't been a good person." And so the situation in the world becomes more deplorable with each passing day.

Fortunately, there is a way to turn this around and it takes neither strength nor money. It takes compassion!

This method requires that everyone abstain from the flesh of living beings and eat only vegetarian food. We must free the animals instead of killing them! If this can be done, then all the world's disasters will vanish. Therefore adopting a compassionate, vegetarian lifestyle is vital. Calamities occur because the universe is filled with the enmity generated by the slaughter. If people would liberate animals rather than killing them, all tendencies towards violence will end.

Meat eating makes one uncompassionate. Hence, if we wish the world to be free of calamities, we must quickly stop killing animals. Only then can we avert these disasters!
